## Additional Terms for ByteBerry Project

This software is part of the ByteBerry ecosystem, an educational project focused on learning microservices architecture, OAuth2 implementation, and Clean Architecture principles.

### Project Context
- **Project Name**: ByteBerry - Sistema de Gestión de Gastos
- **Purpose**: Educational microservices project
- **Target Platform**: Raspberry Pi 5 (ARM64) optimization
- **Architecture**: Clean Architecture with SOLID principles

### Ecosystem Components
This OAuth2 service is designed to work as part of a larger ecosystem:
- OAuth2 Service (this repository)
- Expenses API
- Backend for Frontend (BFF)
- Frontend Application
- Infrastructure & Proxy

### Support and Contact
- **Developer**: JRuvalcabaFSD
- **Support Email**: support@jrmdev.org
- **Project Documentation**: Available in each repository's README.md
- **Docker Images**: Available at https://hub.docker.com/repositories/jruvalcabafsd

### Contribution Guidelines
Contributors must follow:
- Clean Architecture principles
- SOLID design patterns
- Conventional Commits standard
- TypeScript and ESLint configurations
- Test coverage requirements (>80%)
- Docker multi-arch compatibility (AMD64/ARM64)

By using this software, you acknowledge that it is primarily an educational project and may require additional configuration for production use.